<h3>Biography</h3>
<p>Patrick J. Shannon brings more than four decades of experience serving individuals in Murrysville and the surrounding communities. His practice focuses on estate planning and estate administration, where he draws on a career spent helping clients navigate wills, trusts, powers of attorney, probate, and inheritance matters. Patrick's depth of experience allows him to anticipate issues and guide clients through even the most complex estate situations with confidence.</p>
<p>Before joining Ament Law Group, Patrick operated a successful solo practice in Murrysville, where he built a loyal client base through consistent, honest, and personalized legal services. His decision to join Ament Law Group reflects a shared commitment to community-focused representation. His presence strengthens the firm's mission of delivering top-tier legal services that are local and accessible — allowing clients to avoid the inconvenience of urban travel while receiving the quality of counsel typically found in larger markets.</p>
<p>A graduate of Duquesne University School of Law, Patrick has spent his entire career rooted in the Murrysville area, cultivating long-standing relationships that span generations. His addition further enhances Ament Law Group's estate practice and deepens the firm's connection to the local community.</p>
<p>Outside the office, Patrick enjoys spending time with his wife, Stephanie, and their family, and remains actively engaged in the Murrysville community. He is passionate about providing thoughtful, ethical, and thorough legal counsel — guiding clients with clarity and care through every stage of life and legacy planning.</p>
